# ResourceManagerSystem

## Purpose
On the first frame, loads all textures, fonts, shaders, UI layouts, sound clips, JSON assets, 3D
models, render targets, and the text-to-image model assets (checkpoints, LoRAs, ControlNets, VAEs,
OpenPose skeletons, matting models) from `Assets/Engine/ResourcesManifest.json` and
`Assets/App/ResourcesManifest.json`, then creates ResourceMapSingletonComponent containing the fully
populated asset maps. On every subsequent
frame it drains any RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest, registering each generated image as a Texture2D in
the existing texture map under its caller-assigned UUID (so a generated image becomes an ordinary
texture). The first-frame load is guarded by a presence check; the registration drain runs in steady
state.

Render targets are pathless manifest entries (`{id, width, height}`): the created offscreen target is
stored in the render-target map and its colour buffer is registered in the texture map under the same
UUID, so 2D draws can sample the 3D pass's output as an ordinary texture (ADR 0007).

Checkpoints/LoRAs/ControlNets/VAEs are recorded as resolved file paths only (the diffusion backend loads
the weights, not the engine); matting models likewise are paths only, loaded by the matting backend
(onnxruntime) from the `mattingModels` manifest category under the `ImageGeneration` folder (ADR 0012);
OpenPose skeletons are parsed into pose resources. Generated images arrive as
RGB and are expanded to RGBA when registered as textures (ADR 0008); the RGB pixels are also retained as
an Input Image under the same UUID so a later generation can re-feed the result as an img2img init or
chroma background (ADR 0011) — this is what lets a multi-step pipeline chain one step's output into the
next.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read / write | Presence-check guards the one-time load; in steady state generated textures are inserted into the existing map |
| RegisterGeneratedTextureRequestOneFrameComponent | read | Each carries a generated image + target UUID to register as a texture |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once with all asset maps (textures, shaders, fonts, UI layouts, sounds, JSON, models, render targets, checkpoints, LoRAs, ControlNets, VAEs, OpenPose skeletons, matting models); thereafter modified in place to register generated textures (also retained as input images, ADR 0011) |
